channel.title: DTO
channel.description: This is a randomly ordered feed of the most recent entries from DTO, skipping any feeds with errors.

item.title: U.S. and China agree to slash tariffs for 90 days in major trade breakthrough
item.description: The U.S. and China on Monday agreed to suspend most tariffs on each other's goods in a move that shows a thawing of trade tensions.

item.title: Trump poised to accept Qatar jet gift as Air Force One
item.description: Reports of the gift comes just before President Trump is set to travel to the Middle East this week, with a stop in Qatar.

item.title: Economic calendar: Inflation data and Fed remarks among week’s highlights
Trump says China will 'open up' to U.S. businesses, suspend trade barriers
item.description: President Donald Trump said China "agreed to open itself up to American business" after they struck a deal to temporarily slash tariffs.

item.title: Dow set to exit correction territory and vanquish post–‘liberation day’ decline

Iran and the US conclude a 4th round of negotiations over Tehran’s nuclear program in Oman
item.description: Trump has repeatedly threatened to unleash airstrikes targeting Iran's program if a deal isn't reached.

item.title: White House announces U.S.-China trade deal, offers few details
item.description: The Geneva talks come after President Trump slapped 145% tariffs on U.S. imports from China and Beijing retaliated with a 125% levy on U.S. goods.
